Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in St. Lucia. The St. Lucian authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
Travel restrictions
On 15 March, the Government of St Lucia has announced that effective from 17 March, until further notice, any non-St Lucian national with a travel history in mainland China, Hong Kong, Republic of Korea, Japan, Singapore, Italy, France, Germany, Spain, Iran or the UK within 14 days will not be permitted entry into St Lucia. From 16 March, cruise vessels will not be permitted to dock in St Lucia.
For information on how to return to the UK from St Lucia, see Return to the UK.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
